{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f3d824c5-cd58-4ef2-b532-f0284b91b527","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as **skipped/ignored** (not failed) in test results, preserving your reason string.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a465e025-ca06-4798-abf7-321f1ec19c05","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":303,"requestId":"7C1E:11A664:1237493:14A95D9:69F9436F"},"id":"993d203c-faa2-4a5b-ac2d-3014468a5412","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:10:14.187Z","parentId":"30e0d39c-2ec8-4dc6-af7a-d40e0678431c"}
